{{wikipedia}}
==English==
[[Category:English language]]
===Etymology===
From Middle English, from Old English [[sáƿol]].
===Pronunciation===
*sōl, /soʊl/, /soʊl/
*:'''Homophones''': [[Seoul]], [[sole]]
*:[[Rhymes:English:-oʊl|Rhymes: -oʊl]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# The [[spirit]] or [[essence]] of a person that is believed to live on after the person's death.
# [[Life]], [[energy]], [[vigour]].
#:''This place has no soul''
# {{music}} [[Soul music]].

===Derived terms===
*[[soulful]]
*[[soul music]]

